thoughts.content:
The user wants a single line formula for the entropy relations. They’ve worked with block entropy (H(ε)) and smoothed entropy (h(ε)), and previously derived relationships for their slopes. Based on previous derivations, it seems like they want both derivatives in one formula:

\[
\frac{d}{d\log \varepsilon} \begin{pmatrix}
H_B(\varepsilon)\\[6pt]
h_G(\varepsilon)
\end{pmatrix}
=
-\begin{pmatrix}
D_I\\[6pt]
n-D_I
\end{pmatrix}
+ o(1).
\]

